ur]] on 5 April 2019 and was completed by July in [[London]].\n\nThe film was theatrically released in India on 13 March 2020.<ref name=\"release date\">{{cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/bollywood/story/angrezi-medium-to-release-a-week-earlier-on-march-13-gunjan-saxena-delayed-for-a-month-1647277-2020-02-17|title=Angrezi Medium to release a week earlier on March 13|publisher=India Today|date=17 February 2020|accessdate=17 February 2020}}</ref> With its theatrical performance affected by the closing of cinemas due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], plans for a re-release were cancelled and the film was made available digitally less than a month after its release on [[ Disney+ Hotstar]]<ref name=\"hotstar\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/irrfan-khan-s-angrezi-medium-premieres-online-after-being-pulled-out-from-theatres-due-to-lockdown/story-MtvgOQQh3aM74ZPZr3fjWN.html|title=Irrfan Khan\u2019s Angrezi Medium premieres online after being pulled out from theatres due to lockdown|website=[[Hindustan Times]]|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nChampak ([[Irrfan Khan]]), an unassuming sweet shop owner and single father is set to fulfill his daughter's dream to study in [[London]]. However, certain misadventures lead him and his family on a new quest, one which renews their relationships and bonds.This is Irfan's last film before Passing away on 29th April 2020.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Irrfan Khan]] as Champak Bansal\n* [[Kareena Kapoor Khan]] as Officer Naina Kohli \n* [[Radhika Madan]] as Tarika Bansal\n* [[Deepak Dobriyal]] as Gopi Bansal \n* [[Dimple Kapadia]] as Mrs. Sampada Kohli\n* [[Ranvir Shorey]] as Balashankar Tripathi / Bablu\n* [[Pankaj Tripathi]] as Tony \n* [[Kiku Sharda]] as Gajju\n* [[Manu Rishi]] as Bheluram Bansal\n* [[Zakir Hussain (actor)|Zakir Hussain]] as Judge Chedda\n* [[Meghna Malik]] as Principal\n* [[Poorvi Jain]] as Rashi Bansal\n* [[Manish Gandhi]] as Advait\n* [[Tillotama Shome]] as Con